Commentary.Commentary: Right then! Sri Lanka have a massive lead in their hands but they know that the job is not done yet and they will need to bowl as well as they have batted. Whereas, the hosts know that their work is cut out for them and will look to bat strong and apply pressure on the bowling attack of the Lankans. Which team comes out on top? Will the hosts bat well or will Sri Lanka show some good work with the ball in hand? Join us in a short while to find out.

The bowling by the South Africans was not the best at the start as they bowled too many loose deliveries and de Silva and Chandimal did well to take full toll of it. Towards the end of Day 1, the hosts did well to pick up a couple of wickets and at the start of Day 2, they did well to wrap up the Lankan innings early on. Lutho Sipamla and Wiaan Mulder were the pick of the lot where the former got a 4-fer and the latter got a 3-fer. They will still be disappointed that they could not reduce them to a lower total.

Sri Lanka started off poorly but then Dhananjaya de Silva and Dinesh Chandimal did well to stitch a good partnership to take them to safer shores. But then bad news struck as de Silva was injured and could not continue and at the start of Day 2, Lutho Sipamla did well to mop up the rest of the batters and Sri Lanka finish just around the 400-run mark.

Some good work by the hosts in the first hour of Day 2 sees them dismiss the Sri Lankans for 396. The visitors will be disappointed that they could not cross the 400-run mark but they will be happy heading into the shed at the end of their batting.

OUT! CAUGHT! Four-fer for Sipamla and Sri Lanka are all done for 396/9 as de Silva has been retired hurt! That seemed that it would be dropped but the man there does well to hold onto it on the fourth attempt. A back of a length ball around off, Kumara thinks about playing and then leaving and in the end, leaves his bat hanging, the ball takes the outside edge and goes to the slip region, were Rassie does well to take it on the fourth attempt after the ball seemed to be popping out of his hands.
Bouncer outside off, Lahiru sits under this one.
On middle, worked to the long on region for one.
On off, pushed to the mid off region. Shanaka refuses to take the single.
SIX! Banged away! Sri Lanka move to 395 now! A back of a length ball and on off, Shanaka pulls this one to the deep mid-wicket region for a biggie.
Outside off, punched to deep point for a single.
Down the leg side, Lahiru misses his flick.
On middle, clipped to fine leg for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, DS misses his poke.
Another length ball outside off, moves away after pitching, Dasun throws his bat at this but again, misses his shot.
SWING AND A MISS! On a length on off, Shanaka swings his blade but misses the shot.
On off, pushed to the off side. A successful over for the hosts comes to an end. Just a run and two wickets off it.
On off, pushed to covers.
Back of a length and on off, Lahiru blocks this one out.
Sadly, no hat-trick for him! On a length on off, Kumara blocks this one out. Also, a No Ball.
Who's in now? Lahiru Kumara,  it is.

OUT! TIMBER! What did Sipamla have for breakfast? He seems to be all up and ready for Day 2 and he has already picked 2 wickets in 2 balls now! He is also on a hat-trick now. Again, a length ball around the off pole, Fernando looks to block this one out but the ball misses his blade and goes onto rattle the off stump. He gets his third wicket of the game and it looks like the South Africans will be out to bat real soon.
Vishwa Fernando comes in now.

OUT! CAUGHT! The decision to bring on Sipamla has paid dividends for the hosts and Sri Lanka lose their first wicket of Day 2! Lutho bowls this on a good length around the fourth stump channel, Rajitha is tempted into having a poke at this and does so. He can only induce an outside edge and the ball goes to the slip cordon, where Dean Elgar takes the catch.
On off, blocked.
Lutho Sipamla is back into the attack.

NOT OUT! South Africa lose a review in the process and Shanaka survives! On a length on middle and leg, Shanaka looks to put bat to ball but misses to get hit on the pads. There is an appeal but no says the umpire. De Kock wants to take this one upstairs. Replays roll in and the ball is going down leg and is missing the wickets. The hosts lose a review as well.

South Africa review! The Proteas' go up in tandem for this lbw appeal but no says the umpire. They want to check this upstairs. Shanaka is the man in question. Looks real close. Let's see what the replays say.
An absolute jaffa! A length ball, just around the off pole, Dasun is looking to block this one but the ball just misses his outside edge and goes into de Kock's mitts.
On off, pushed to the mid on region.
Outside off, left alone by Shanaka.
Short of a length and around off, Dasun looks to block this one out but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
On a length on off, pushed back to the bowler.
A bouncer on middle, Kasun looks to block this one but misses to get hit on the body. Must have stung slightly but nothing too serious. 13 off this over for the visitors.
Outside off, cut to third man for one.

SIX! GREAT SHOT! Shanaka is looking in some touch here! There was a man there but he only sees the ball fly over him! A back of a length ball and around off, Shanaka makes room and slams it over the backward point fence for a biggie.
Outside off, left alone.

SIX! FIFTY FOR SHANAKA! His first one in Test cricket and this is something that he will remember! A great shot to get to this milestone as well! Slightly shorter in length and on off, Shanak swivels and hammers this one over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
On off, pushed to point.
Full ball and around off, Rajitha works this to the man at point.
On off, Kasun defends this one.
Outside off, no shot offered to this by Rajitha.

EDGED...SHORT! A good chance to break this partnership but this one is just short! On a length around off, Kasun looks to block but the ball takes the edge and goes towards du Plessis at first slip, but it falls just short of him.
Length delivery around the fourth stump line, Kasun misses his drive, looking to play away from his body. Just where Ngidi needs to be bowling.
Length ball and on off, Kasun is solid in his defense.
Short around off, DS sways away from this one.
On off, pushed to point for a single.

FOUR BYES! Ohhh...Nasty delivery! A bumper around off, Rajitha does well to sway away and let this one through. Quinton takes a leap of faith but it is not enough to stop the ball. The ball races away to the ropes.
Yorker on off, pushed to the cover region. The batters think about the single but then decide not to take it in the end.
On middle, clipped to the leg side for a single.
FOUR! On a length on off, Shanaka guides this one through the backward point region for a boundary.
On a good length outside off, Rajitha looks to block this one out but misses.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length on off, played to the cover region.
Outside off, left alone.
Length and on off, Rajitha misses his block.
On off, tucked through square leg for a single.
Three to end the over! On a length on off, guided through backward point for three.
Length on off, pushed to the cover region.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
On off, blocked to the cover region.
Good length outside off, Shanaka shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length and around the middle pole, Dasun clips this one through the mid-wicket region for a couple.
Outside off, pushed to the cover region for a single.
Short of a length and on off, tapped to point.
SIX! First biggie of the day and it is Shanaka who sends it straight to the empty stands! A short ball on middle and leg, Shanaka swivels and pulls this one to the fine leg region for a maximum.
BEATEN! Ngidi has started off nicely! A good length delivery, just around the fourth stump channel, Dasun looks for the defensive push but gets beaten all ends up.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, clipped towards the mid-wicket region for a couple.
Who will partner Nortje with the ball? It will be Lungi Ngidi from the other end.
Dot to end! On a length on off, KR looks to play at this but misses.

FOUR BYES! There's a bumper from Nortje and there was nothing that de Kock could do about this! A bouncer on middle, Rajitha ducks under this one and de Kock jumps but is not able to catch it and it runs away to the ropes.
Back of a length on off, Kasun looks to play at this but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
SWING AND A MISS! A length delivery around off, Kasun looks to work at this but misses it completely.
FOUR! First boundary of the day and it is off Rajitha's bat! On a length on off, Rajitha looks to drive but it takes an outside edge and flies past gully and into the ropes for a boundary.
LEG BYE! First runs off the day, not of the bat though! On a length on middle, Shanaka looks to work it to the leg side but he misses and the ball rolls to the leg side. A leg bye is collected.

Right then! We are all ready to begin the action for Day 2! The overnight batters for Sri Lanka, Dasun Shanaka and Kasun Rajitha are striding out into the middle, followed by the South African players who are spreading out on the field. Anrich Nortje will be starting with the ball for the hosts. Off we go...

Lungi Ngidi is up for a chat. Says that the boundary percentage conceded by South Africa was high. Feels the numbers are pretty high and that the bowlers were searching for wickets, instead of being more patient. Feels that his team can still swing the game back in their favour. Adds that he was working on the away shape, making sure the wrist position was in good shape. Says that it was unfortunate that he could not get the edge that he was looking for. States that the first session is crucial for them as they need to now look at netting the remaining wickets. However, Lungi also adds that it is important not to overdo stuff.

Pitch Report - How is the surface on Day 2? Shaun Pollock and Vernon Philander are out in the middle for the Pitch Report. The former feels that there is plenty for the seamers and adds that there will continue to be a lot of movement. Vernon feels the bowlers must land a string of deliveries in that area where the ball misbehaves a little. Shaun states that (examining the area where the ball misbehaves) there is a little grass present. Philander says that more cracks will open up on Days 3 and 4 and Pollock feels the ball will misbehave more from the Pavilion end. On tips to the batsmen, Shaun Pollock states that the batters must be aware of the grass present. Expects Sri Lanka to put up a quality bowling, whenever they come out to bowl.

Hello and welcome to our coverage of Day 2 of the 1st Test between Sri Lanka and South Africa. 400. 400! That is what the Lankans would be telling themselves to get, at the very least. They have batted well so far and would have done even better had Dhananjaya not gotten injured. And what compounds matters further for the visitors is the fact that the injured de Silva will now no longer be available for the rest of the Test series. That will be a huge blow for the Lankans. Coming back to the match though, the overnight batters would now look to do well, while South Africans would look to clean the remaining wickets up as quickly as possible. Stay tuned as a gripping first session of Day 2 awaits us...

Can the Lankans get to 400? Can Dhananjaya de Silva rest the whole night and somehow come to bat on Day 2? The tourists will hope that is the case. Not saying that 400 could be enough, given that the pitch usually gets better to bat on from Day 2. But it will be a psychological boost for sure. The opening hour could have plenty of action, so do not miss it. We bid you goodbye for now. Join us back on Sunday, 27th December, 2020 at 10 am local (0800 GMT). ADIOS! TAKE CARE!

The saying goes - Never lose hope. Keep trying. One such South African gave it his all. Wiaan Mulder, against the run of play, got Chandimal and Dickwella in quick succession and the Proteas found something to take away from the day, in the dying minutes of the final session. Mulder was the pick of the bowlers, with 3 wickets but the others might feel a bit unlucky, as they beat the bat quite often. The home side will hope to finish off this innings quickly on Sunday.

It wasn't the best of starts for the Lankans as batters kept getting in but then getting out, mainly to soft dismissals. They were 54/3 before Dhananjaya de Silva and Dinesh Chandimal got the Lankans on track. It was during this period that the ball got softer and the Proteas lost their sting. The visitors were looking really good but then de Silva suffered a thigh strain and had to retire hurt. Even then, Niroshan Dickwella came out and staged a decent stand with Chandimal.

Bravo, Sri Lanka. After making a brave decision to bat first, they have not only endured the whole day, but also scored at 4 an over, getting almost 350 runs! Coach Mickey Arthur is pumped up and he certainly believes that round 1 of the Boxing Day has gone to Sri Lanka.
Hits him again. On a length, around middle, Rajitha looks to work it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the arm. A look at the umpires and that will be it. STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Full and around off, pushed towards cover.
Full and outside off, perfect line, perfect length, makes the batsman play, defeats him but cannot draw the edge!
On a length, outside off, watchfully defended towards point.

Understandably, Rajitha wants to make sure that the medical staff is made to come out to the middle. Last few minutes of the day, he would want this to be the final over. The magic spray goes out on his left hand. Shanaka asks whether he is okay and Rajitha responds smilingly. 1 minute gone by in all that. 3 more left.
Ouch.That has kicked off from nowhere. On a length, outside off, Rajitha looks to defend but the ball rears up from there and raps him on the glove. That would be really painful.
Full and outside off, driven to the left of Temba Bavuma at cover for a single.
Outside off, pushed towards mid off.
Pitched up, outside off, pushed towards cover for a run.
Outside off, on a length, but pretty wide, let through.
Unplayabale again. Back of a length, outside off, Shanaka looks to feel for it but misses. 39 balls left in the day, but just 8 minutes to go.
Almost shows his back to the bowler but somehow, get it off the inner half of the bat towards fine leg! Takes the single and is happy to be at the other end.

Another one beats the edge. The inside one this time. On a length, around off, Rajitha looks to work it to the leg side but the ball shapes back in, goes in between bat and body and towards the keeper. Nortje gives a long stare to Rajitha.
Full and around off, driven towards mid on.
Full and around off, Dasun gets forward and pushes it towards mid on.
Full and jut outside off, Shanaka look to defend but is beaten by the late away shape. Get the feeling that something is going to give.
Another beauty. On a length, outside off, DS looks to defend but then, the ball shapes away. Is squared up and the ball beats the outside edge.
Fuller and just outside off, Dasun prods to defend but misses as the ball shapes away.
Oh dear... what was that? A length ball, outside off, Shanaka swings like there is no tomorrow and misses.
Full and outside off, KR hangs his bat well inside the line.

UPPISH, FOUR! Almost a wicket. Outside off, on a length, Rajitha is drawn forward as he looks to push. The ball flies off the edge but is wide of gully. Races to the third man fence. 49 balls left in the day but just 15 minutes to go.
Full and outside off, the tempter, Kasun is tempted to drive but misses the outswinger by a long margin.
Outside off, on a length, Rajitha seems to be in body-preservation mode, as he backs away to the leg side and slashes blindly. Misses.
Full and wide outside off, crashed away but straight to deep point. A single taken.
And he starts with a ripper too. Nice seam position, upright, landing it on a length, just around off stump, making Shanaka play and then getting it to shape away, to beat the outside edge.
We have a bowling change, as expected. Anrich Nortje returns. 16-3-53-1 so far.
That was a ripper! Frustration for Ngidi. He wants Rajitha to play, gets Rajitha to play, but then bowls wider outside off. And then, sees the ball kicking up and beat the outside edge.
On a length wide outside off, easy leave for Rajitha.
Back of a length, outside off, pushed towards cover for a single.
On a length, around off, solidly defended.
Outside off, on a length, shouldered arms to.
Good start. Movement through the air, fuller in length, outside off, Shanaka looks to drive but misses. 59 balls left in the day but only 22 minutes to go.
THE SECOND NEW BALL IS AVAILABLE AND IS TAKEN. Lungi Ngidi to make the first use of it. 13-1-52-1 so far. 23 minutes to go with the extended half hour of play already in use.
Full and around off, solidly kept out.
Outside off, chopped down to point for a single.
Comes down the track again, but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.

SIX! First one of the innings! Shanaka is chancing his arm in probably the last few overs before the second new ball. Full and outside off, Dasun gets down and swings it over wide long on! Moves to 20 from 31 balls. The stand moves to 10 from 17 deliveries.
Tossed up, outside off, Shanaka comes down the track and pushes it towards cover.
Much fuller, outside off, driven towards cover.

Bizarre, very bizarre! The South African slip cordon is smiling. On a length, wide outside off, KR misjudges the length really badly and ducks. The ball barely bounces and is taken at shin level by de Kock.
On a length, outside off, helped through mid-wicket for a run.
This one darts back in but Kasun does well to flick it towards fine leg for a single. 59 minutes left in the day (extended), 69 balls to go.
Another beauty. On a length, outside off, Rajitha looks to defend but the ball straightens and goes past the outside edge and over the stumps as well.
Full and outside off, Shanaka looks to drive but mistimes it towards cover.
Full and outside off, worked straight to short mid-wicket.
Full and around off, worked through mid-wicket for a run.
Around off, pushed towards cover.
Risky leave. Outside off, Kasun comes forward, then goes back, thinking that the ball will turn. But the naughty ball doesn't and just goes past the off stump as Rajitha lets it go!
Slowly tossed up outside off, Rajitha lunges to defend but is beaten.
Full and outside off, driven towards long off for a single.
Around off, on a length, well blocked out.

Whoa! That has jagged back a long way! Sipamla has got a spring in his step with that wicket. The ball is 76 overs old but still jagging around. On a length, outside off, Kasun looks to defend but the ball jags back in a long way, cuts the batsman into half, goes over the stumps and still moves a long way. De Kock does really well to dive to his left to take that. 65 minutes left in the day (extended), 79 balls to go.
On a length, outside off, cuts back in, Rajitha shoulders arms on length.
Kasun Rajitha walks in at number 8, replacing Hasaranga.

OUT! BOWLED! Sipamla is on the board as Hasaranga chops one on. A length ball, outside off, Wanindu plays away from his body, looking to push but is defeated by the extra bounce. The ball takes the inside edge and hits the top of the bails. Sipamla is delighted. He has toiled hard all day and eventually, got a wicket.
Outside off, on a length, solidly defended.
Full and outside off, Hasaranga looks to drive but misses.
Around off, pushed towards long off for a run.
FOUR! BELLIGERENT! He is not messing around. Little bit of flight, outside off, Hasaranga gets down on a knee and slog sweeps it over mid-wicket. The stand moves to 23 from 32 balls.
Comes from a wider angle outside off, bowls it around middle, Hasaranga defends.
Short and outside off, cut behind point for a single.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, Shanaka comes down the track and hits it straight back. Maharaj looks to pick up and throw but hurts himself. 89 balls left in the day.
Outside off, on a length, moving away, left alone.
Full and straight, swinging in, driven straight to mid on. Is there some reverse happening?
On a length, punched through the covers for a brace again.
Outside off, punched through the covers for a couple. Hasaranga moves to 11 at run-a-ball.
That one kicks up. Outside off, on a length, Hasaranga comes forward to defend but the ball rears up all of a sudden and pings him on the gloves. Wanindu wrings his hand in pain.
Around middle, helped towards short mid-wicket.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
Fuller and around off, wristed towards short mid-wicket.
Around off, watchfully blocked out.
FOUR! What a shot. Flighted, fuller, outside off, Shanaka comes down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket. Moves to 11 from 20 balls.
Around off, solidly defended.
Full and outside off, Hasaranga looks to push and run to the off side but is sent back.
Full and outside off, pushed uppishly through point for a run.
A bit too straight, helped behind square leg for a single.
Around off, WH feels for the ball and is beaten again.

And that is precisely why the bowler should not be too unhappy with the previous boundary. This is pitched up, outside off, encouraging Wanindu to drive and then is shaped away to beat the outside edge.
FOUR! MARVELLOUS! Full and outside off, Hasaranga comes on the front foot and drives it on the up through mid off! The bowler should not be too unhappy.
Down the leg side, flick shot missed.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.
Comes down the track and drives but back to Maharaj.
Full and around off, driven back towards the bowler.
Full and around off, Shanaka looks to defend but the ball sneaks off the inside edge towards short fine leg.
Straight as an arrow, blocked towards short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.

EDGED, FOUR! Why isn't the slip cordon packed? Full and outside off, Hasaranga looks to drive but the ball moves away and takes the outside edge. It goes to where third slip would have been, to the third man fence.
On a length outside off, left alone.
Outside off, Hasaranga slashes hard but misses.
Into the lower order. Or all-rounders. Or bowlers who can bat. Wanindu Hasaranga is the first of them.

OUT! LBW! Sri Lanka lose both, a review and Dickwella, with the second new ball nearing. A pretty straight ball, which at first, seemed to be pitching outside leg. Niroshan was trying to work it to the leg side but the ball straightened a touch and kept low as well, hitting him on the pads. Mulder appealed and up went Erasmus' finger! ND immediately took the review, suggesting the ball was pitched outside leg. Ultra Edge seemed to detect a spike when ball passed the bat but closer look at the replays suggested that the bat was well away from the ball. And then came Ball Tracker. Pitched JUST about in line and hitting the stumps. Big wicket.

LBW appeal and given! But Dickwella has gone up straightaway. Did it pitch outside leg? Doesn't seem so, as per the first replay. Was there an inside edge? Nope. Ball Tracker comes and Dickwella has to go!
FOUR! MAJESTIC! Overpitched, outside off, Dickwella leans into the shot and drives it through the covers. The fielder dives to his right, but misses the ball.
Full and down the leg side, helped towards mid-wicket.
There is a change in bowling. It is Wiaan Mulder. 15-3-50-2 so far.
Angled into the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, Shanaka works it to mid-wicket.
Shorter and aroud off, Dickwella strokes it to covers.
Another tossed up ball on middle, it is flicked to mid-wicket.
On middle, Dickwella works it to mid-wicket.
The sweep comes out! It is hit to the man at short fine leg.
Keshav Maharaj is back!
A single to end the over! Short and on the body, this is pulled towards fine leg. It goes on the bounce so just the one.
Goes shorter in length this time, Dickwella hops and works it to mid-wicket.
On off, Dickwella gets right behind the line and pushes it to mid off.
Shorter in length and on middle, Dickwella stays back and defends it onto the ground.
On middle, this is pushed back to the bowler.
Shorter and outside off, Dickwella initially looks to play the upper cut but then realizes there is a fielder for that, pulls his bat back.

DRINKS! So South Africa have finally managed to get the breakthrough! They would really hope to build on this. Also, they would love another one before the second new ball. Sri Lanka on the other hand, would want to continue the good work done by them so far. They would know another good partnership and they will well and truly be on top of this game. Will they get one more or will South Africa fightback?
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Length again and on middle, defended.
Outside off, not played at.
Fuller and around off, Shanaka looks to drive but it goes off the outer half through covers for two.
Good length and on off, Dasun keeps it out.
FOUR! A lovely shot to get off the mark! This is fuller and outside off, Shanaka leans into it and creams it through covers. No chance of stopping that.
Good fielding! This is fuller and around off, Dickwella pushes it towards mid off. The fielder at extra cover runs to his left and stops it.
One more bumper and on middle, Dickwella lets it go over him.
One more short one and on middle, Dickwella lets it go to the keeper.
A short one and on middle, Dickwella evades it nicely.
On middle, it is defended nicely.
That has stayed low! Almost another one for South Africa! This lands outside off, Dickwella looks to defend but is stays low and sneaks below the bat.
Some movement now! It is on a length and around off, shapes away. Shanaka lets it be.
Outside off, not played at.
Dasun Shanaka walks out to bat!

OUT! TAKEN! That is a nasty delivery! An unplayable one, exactly what was needed to dismiss Chandimal because he was looking solid as ever. This once again, like quite a few deliveries in this gamne, rises out of nowhere. Lands on off and then takes off. Chandimal looks to fend it away by taking a hand off the handle. It flies off the glove to the widish frist slip fielder. End of a lovely knock from Chandimal but South Africa will hope this opens the floodgates.
Length again and on off, Chandimal pushes it to covers.
On off again, this is pushed to mid off.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
One more bumper, it is ducked under.
FOUR BYES! Way too short and on middle, Chandimal ducks under it. It goes well over the keeper for a boundary.
Another one on middle, Dickwella works it uppishly but in the gap in the mid-wicket region for one.
On middle again, this is defended onto the ground.
Shorter and around off, this is dropped towards point for one.
Bangs it short first up on middle, it is ducked under.
Nortje is on! He is coming from around the wicket so it is time for some short ball bowling!
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on off, it is guided to point.
FOUR! Smartly played! This is short and on middle, Dickwella waits for it and then plays it late. He plays the upper cut, it goes over the keeper for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, Dickwella pushes it towards cover.
A single to follow the boundary! On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
FOUR! Gift for Chandimal! It is on the pads, Chandimal says thank you very much as he works it fine on the leg side for a boundary.
One more short ball is cut towards deep point for one. This time there is protection in the deep.
FOUR! Short ball and put away! Can't bowl there to Chandimal. It is shorter and outside off, it is slapped through point for a boundary.
Outside off and shorter in length. Chandimal looks to pull but misses.
Shorter and around off, Chandimal pushes it to covers.
Fuller and on off, it is pushed to mid off.
Angled into middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! SHOT! On a length on off, Dickwella lofts this one over the mid on region for a boundary.
Length ball on the middle pole, worked straight to mid on. Dickwella first agreed for the single but then sent Dinesh back.
Down the leg side again by Mulder, Dickwella again misses his flick.
Slips this down the leg side, Dickwella misses his tuck away.
On a length on leg, tucked away through square leg for a brace.
On off, pushed to covers for a single.
Good length delivery around off, Niroshan is solid in his defense.
On middle, DC works it back towards the bowler and Sipamla gets his hands on this one to slow the ball down. Just a single.
On a full length around the off pole, Dinesh squeezes this one through covers for a brace.
Back of a length and around off, punched to the man at mid off. Dinesh is quick to say 'No run, no run'.
SLASH AND A MISS! On a length outside off, Chandimal looks to cut this one away but misses it altogether.
On off, driven to covers.
Slips this down the leg side, Dickwella misses his flick though.
On off, pushed to covers.
FOUR! Dickwella sends one past the ropes now! On a length outside off, Dickwella slices this one through the backward point region to find the ropes. 250 up for Sri Lanka as well.
LEG BYE! On middle, DC looks to flick but misses and the ball takes the pads and goes to the leg side. The batters collect a leg bye.
Short of a length and around off, Chandimal pushes this one to the mid off region and looks for the single but is sent back by Dickwella.
Good length ball on off, Dinesh works this to the cover region where Bavuma dives well and stops this one.
Outside off again, guided to gully.
Outside off, Dinesh raises his willow and lets this one through.
Good length delivery outside the off pole, pushed to the point region and the batters cross ends.
On middle, nudged to mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, left alone by Niroshan.
PLAY AND A MISS! On a length outside off, Dickwella looks to drive but only connects his blade with thin air.
Lutho Sipamla is back on. 9-0-56-0 are his numbers so far.
On off, pushed to covers.

Not what the hosts were planning for when they came out after Lunch. They have not been able to scalp a single wicket in this entire session, apart from the injury to de Silva. Some change is definitely required for the Proteas as they will need some wickets and will need to stem the flow of runs if they want to end the day strongly. Which team comes out on top after Tea? Join us on the other side.

The visitors started off the second session in good fashion. They were attacking the loose balls and were letting go of the balls that could do them some damage. Chandimal and de Silva also stitched a 100-run partnership but were forced to stop as de Silva was in some pain and could not continue. Even though, this was a cause of concern, their batting continued on with Dickwella taking de Silva's place. Chandimal also reached his half-century before Tea and Sri Lanka have also crossed the 200 run mark.

If the last session was even-stevens, then this session would go the way of Sri Lanka. They have not lost a wicket in the second session but they have lost Dhananjaya de Silva due to an injury, which will concern the camp of Sri Lanka. But overall, they will be really pleased with how things have panned out so far.

But then, they lost three wickets in quick succession and it looked like they lost their way slightly. But the duo of De Silva and Chandimal have done well to battle it out there and not lose any more wickets.

Outside off, Kusal pushes this to point.
FOUR! Perera has started off strongly! On a length on middle, Perera clips this one through the short fine leg region into the ropes.
An appeal for LBW but turned down! A back of a length ball on middle and leg, KP looks to tuck this away but misses to get hit on the pads. A loud appeal follows but no says the umpire.
On off, pushed to the off side.
Anrich Nortje into the attack now.
One to end! On middle, worked through square leg.
Good length ball outside off, Perera looks to cut but it takes the inside half of the bat and it goes past the leg stump. A couple taken as the ball rolls to fine leg.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
On middle, worked to square leg again.
On middle, nudged to square leg.
FOUR! Short ball outside off, Perera lofts this one over the cover region for a boundary. Kusal is not going to miss out on these.
Length ball on off, pushed to the off side.
FOUR! Beautifully played by Mendis! Slightly overpitched around the off pole, Mendis plays it with a straight bat and through mid off and the ball runs away to the ropes. Confident start by Kusal.
Short ball around off, Mendis thinks of playing the pull but then decides against it. No Ball given.
FOUR! A freebie to Mendis and he opens his account in this game! A slow short ball outside off, Mendis slashes this one over the cover region to find the ropes.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, worked to mid-wicket for a quick run.
Overpitched around the off pole, Kusal pushes this to the mid off region.
Outside off, Mendis looks to play at that but decides not to, right at the end. A good over for the Proteas comes to an end.
Who comes in now? Kusal Mendis is in.

OUT! TIMBER! DRAGGED ON! The first wicket falls for the visitors and the captain, who had a good start has to walk back now! Karunaratne had a good start but unfortunately for the Lankans, he cannot continue on. Slightly shortish and outside off, Dimuth looks to push this one away but does not move his feet. The ball takes the inside edge and goes onto rattle the stumps behind him.
On middle and leg, slightly behind the good length, the captain looks for the flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
On off, played to the leg side.
Outside off, punched to covers for a single.
Short of a length and on off, KP looks to defend but it takes the edge and goes to the point region.
FOUR! Boundary to end the over! An overpitched delivery and on off, Karunaratne clips this one through mid-wicket and it runs away to the ropes. A good over for the visitors. 10 runs off this.
Bouncer on middle, Dimuth sits under this one.

EDGY FOUR! Not what the skipper was looking to do but he will be happy with the result! On a length on off, Dimuth looks to block this one out but it takes the outside edge and goes in between slips and gully into the third man boundary.
On off, pushed to the leg side.
BEATEN! Ohhh...great bowling by Sipamla! Lands it on a length and around off, Karunaratne looks for the defensive stroke but the ball whizzes past his outside edge and into the keeper's mitts.
On a length on middle, Dimuth clips this through square leg and collects two runs as Ngidi runs across in the deep and stops this from crossing the ropes.
Full ball on off, Perera looks to push this away but it takes the inside edge and hits him on the pads.
Back of a length ball on off, Kusal looks to work this one away but misses again to get hit on the pads.
Slightly straight again, KP looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Good length on off, Perara pushes it towards mid on and the batters take off for a single. There is a throw at the striker's end but it is missed and the batters collect one more. Good running.
On middle, pushed to the square leg region.
A full delivery on off, Kusal pushes it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! A beauty to end the over! On a length on off, Karunaratne looks for the defensive stroke but misses it altogether.
Back of a length on middle, blocked out.
Full ball and on off, DM works it through square leg and the call is for two. They collect two comfortably.
FOUR! The skipper is off to a good start! Straight and on middle again, clipped to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Slightly straight and on the pads, flicked away to the right of fine leg for a couple.

3 LEG BYES! On the pads, Kusal looks to tuck this away but it comes off the thigh pad and goes past de Kock towards the fine leg region. The fielder gives it a chase and stops it before the ropes. Three leg byes collected.
Who partners Ngidi with the new ball? The debutant, Lutho Sipamla is going to bowl from the other end.
Dot to end! On off, pushed to the leg side. 4 from the first over.

FOUR! Sri Lanka and Karunaratne are underway and they do it with some style! Some width offered as this was outside off, the skipper camps back and punches this one through the cover region for a boundary. A good start for Lankans.
On off, pushed to the leg side.
Inward movement noticed! Another back of a length ball on middle and leg, Karunaratne looks to push this to the leg side but the ball nips into Dimuth and hits him on the thigh pad.
Down the leg side, DM misses his tuck away.
Ngidi starts off with a back of a length ball into the left-hander, Dimuth looks to tuck this one away but gets hit high on the thigh pad and the ball rolls to the off side.

Done and dusted with the Anthems! The South African players now make their way onto the field. The Lankan openers Dimuth Karunaratne and Kusal Perera follow. The former will take strike and he will face Lungi Ngidi. Here we go...
Time for the National Anthems! The two teams make their way out for it. Lanka will sing first and then the hosts will follow.

South African skipper, Quinton de Kock, says that they are ready to get going. Adds that Mulder has been in good form in the domestic season and he provides something with the bat as well. States that Sipamla has been bowling well in practice and he is excited to get going. Ends by saying that they want to do well.

The Lankan skipper, Dimuth Karunaratne, says that the wicket is looking good and they know how the wicket will play later on and hence, they want to bat first. Adds that they are not focussing on the past series and they want to do well here. Mentions that they need to play well. Goes onto say that they have not played international cricekt for a while but the boys are ready to go.

South Africa (PLAYING XI) - Aiden Markram, Dean Elgar, Rassie van der Dussen, Faf du Plessis, Quinton de Kock (WK/C), Temba Bavuma, Wiaan Mulder, Keshav Maharaj, Anrich Nortje, Lutho Sipamla, Lungi Ngidi.

Sri Lanka (PLAYING XI) - Dimuth Karunaratne (C), Kusal Perera, Kusal Mendis, Dinesh Chandimal, Dhananjaya de Silva, Niroshan Dickwella (WK), Dasun Shanaka, Wanindu Hasaranga, Vishwa Fernando, Kasun Rajitha, Lahiru Kumara.
TOSS - Up goes the coin and it lands in the favor of Lanka! THEY WILL BAT FIRST!

Mark Boucher is up for an interview. He says that they are trying to learn a lot in the bubble and they have some changes to their squad. Also says that not playing in front of the crowds is not ideal but is happy to be playing cricket in these times. Goes onto say that they are trying to keep the guys as happy as they can. Ends by saying that there are more important things and safety of the players is most important.

Day 1 between New Zealand and Pakistan - done. The first day between India and Australia - done. Test cricket does not end for today as there’s another game which begins on Boxing Day between South Africa and Sri Lanka. It seems like a long time since the two sides played Test cricket. The Lankans though have a fond memory of the last time they came here. The hosts though still are overwhelming favorites heading into the series. Welcome to the coverage. Toss coming up in a bit...

South Africa would look to pick up 2-3 wickets in the end of Day 3 to put pressure on Sri Lanka. On the other hand, Sri Lanka would look to negotiate the 18 overs left in the day's play today. They can only draw this match as a win looks impossible for them from here. Join us for Sri Lanka's second innings in a bit.

Coming to Sri Lanka, Vishwa Fernando and Hasaranga were the pick of the bowlers. They had no answers to the South African batting. Hasaranga took 4 wickets and he was the pick of the bowlers. Vishwa Fernando took three wickets. Even Shanaka bowled well. They lost Lahiru Kumara due to injury and were a bowler short. Even Wanindu Hasaranga got injured but he came back towards the end of the second session. Despite scoring 396 Sri Lanka are on back foot now.

It has been a good batting performance from South Africa. Faf du Plessis missed out on his double century by getting dismissed on 199. He tooked tired out there by playing that shot on 199. His partnership with Temba Bavuma was good and crucial for South Africa at that time. Dean Elgar and Aiden Markram gave them a good start. Both scored fifties.

OUT! CAUGHT! A fine innings from Keshav comes to an end. He has hit 73 from 106 balls. A very fine knock from him. Short ball, outside off, Maharaj backs away and looks to pull that over mid-wicket. But he ends up getting a top edge there. It goes behind square on the off side, where Hasaranga gives chase and takes it later on. SOUTH AFRICA FINISH ON 621 AND LEAD BY 225 RUNS!

DRINKS! Maharaj is still out there and Faf du Plessis missed out on a well deserved double century. He looked tired while playing that shot. On the other hand, Sri Lanka are just one wicket away from wrapping up the innings. Hasaranga has took 4 wickets and would look to end the innings with a five-fer.
A couple here. On off and middle, Lungi works this behind square on the leg side for two.
Full and on off, blocked.

DROPPED! Maharaj telling Lungi Ngidi to calm down here. Hasaranga floats this around off, LN comes forward and strokes it uppishly and firmly towards short mid-wicket. The fielder there, dives forward but fails to hold onto that.
Flighted around off, pushed to the on side.
BEATEN! That is the right length there. Full and outside off, Ngidi prods forward and looks to block but fails to do so there.
Full and around off, KM mishits it down to long on. Surprisingly opts to take a single off the very first ball here.
A single and the lead is now 222. Short ball, Keshav Maharaj goes for the pull. He gets a top edge there but it lands safely in the mid-wicket region. Takes a single and keeps strike.
Outside off, left alone.
SIX! It is a grand shot. Full-blooded swing of the bat. Full toss, Maharaj backs away and swings it mightily over deep square leg for half a dozen.
Wow, that's another excellent ball. KM going after everything here. He moved to the leg side a hint and Vishwa follows him with a full length ball. Keshav swings for the heavens but misses it.
Wow, that's a good ball. It is a good challenging long hop. Keshav Maharaj goes for the pull shot but the bounce on the ball takes it over his flashing blade.
A well-disguised slower ball down the leg side, Maharaj looks to slog it towards deep backward square leg. Misses.
BEATEN! Full and outside off, Lungi prods forward and looks to block but fails to make any sort of connection there.
Full and outside off, hit down to mid off.
Full and outside off, pushed down to long off.
Very full and around off, driven down to mid on.
Lungi Ngidi is the last man in.

OUT! LBW! Lutho Sipalma departs, on the very first ball here. It was the googly, it pitches on off and comes into Lutho. He looks to drive but to the naked eye, he seems to have missed and got hit on the pads. An appeal is put in for the LBW and the on-field umpire, after pondering for a good while, raises his finger. Sipalma, comes down, has a chat with Keshav and decides to take the review there. They have 3 reviews, so no problems in gambling with 1, with nothing much to lose. It is taken upstairs, Ultra Edge indicates that there was no bat there. In comes Ball Tracker and it seals the formality in Lanka's favour. Sipalma has to now walk back.
Flatter and outside off, backs away and cuts it to deep cover. A single. The fielder in the deep fumbles but luckily for Sri Lanka, does not cost them any extra runs.
Lutho Sipamla is the new batsman in.

OUT! CAUGHT! So, are we in for a declaration now? Should not be long, but let's see. Anrich has lasted just 3 deliveries here. And on the 3rd, he has gotten himself out. Just a faint edge here. Fullish and outside off from around the wicket, Nortje looks to drive that through the covers but ends up getting a faint edge off the outer half. It goes behind and Niroshan Dickwella takes the easiest of catches. Fail to understand why the hosts are not declaring here! No point in continuing to push much now.
Fullish and outside off, stabbed to backward point.
On the pads, Keshav Maharaj looks to tickle it down to fine leg but ends up getting it off his pads. It goes down to that region and a leg bye is sneaked in.
Full and outside off, stroked firmly but straight to cover. Right then, are we going to see some aggressive strokeplay from the Saffas now?
Full and down the leg side, Maharaj looks to help it down towards fine leg but fails to make any connection there.
Bouncer but down the leg side, Keshav ducks under it.
Fullish and outside off, tapped to the off side.
Anrich Nortje is the new batsman in.

OUT! TAKEN! Oh my God! Du Plessis! What have you done? He has gone for the glory shot and perished here! The South African dugout cannot believe that. It has been a remarkable innings nonetheless. South Africa are now 609/7 and the lead is 213. Full and around off, Faf du Plessis looks to go big over mid on. Wanted to get to his double with a boundary. Rush of blood maybe? Whatever, the man at mid on, Karunaratne takes it and Faf cannot believe that.

The partnership between these two moves to 133 now. And that is a record. Outside off, hit down to long off for a single. This is now the highest 7th wicket partnership for the South Africans against Sri Lanka.
The quicker one, short and outside off, hurriedly cut to point.
This time, du Plessis is able to nudge it well wide of cover and takes a single. Moves to 199.
A flat legbreak, outside off, punched to cover.
Full and outside off, stroked down to deep cover. Just the single. But Faf will keep strike. He is just 2 shy of his maiden 200 in whites now.
On the pads, clipped to deep square leg for a single.

FOUR! OMG! Keshav Maharaj! What? Hohoho..... the Rainbow Nation's dressing camp is happy alright. Short ball, Keshav stays on the back foot and pulls it ferociously over long on and gets himself a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, guided down to deep backward point for a single. The lead moves to 205. Something more than enough for the Proteas to play around with.
Short and outside off, left alone. This is good from the South Africans. They have amassed a lead, making sure that they do not come out to bat last on this Centurion wicket.
Good length ball around off, defended to point for a dot.
Vishwa Fernando is back on.
Shortish and around off, Maharaj backs away and strokes but finds cover.

FOUR! What a shot! And the 600 is up for the South Africans as well. Short ball, Maharaj goes back and drags this down to the long on boundary. Oh... the Proteas have batted really beautifully here. The lead now moves to 204 and it is a very difficult position, to be a Sri Lankan player.
Keshav defends this on off delivery to the off side.
Fullish and outside off, hit down to long off for a single.

A vociferous appeal for LBW from Dickwella. But there was bat involved there. Flighted on off and middle, du Plessis strides forward and defends it out to the off side. Niroshan Dickwella appeals, thinking it came off the pads, but the umpire smiles it off.
Wanindu floats this outside off, stroked firmly but straight to cover.
Full delivery on off, Maharaj drives it to point.
Good length ball on off, Maharaj defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length on middle, Maharaj pushes it to mid on.
Good length delivery down the leg side, Maharaj lets it go.
Full ball on middle, du Plessis pushes it towards mid on for a single.
Full delivery on middle, du Plessis flicks it to mid-wicket.
Fullish and just outside off, hit down to long off for a single.
Flatter and around off, tapped to the off side.
Outside off, nudged to point.
Flatter and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
This one is hit to deep point for a couple.

NOT OUT! It was going to be that way when the third umpire took that long. Floats this just outside off, du Plessis prods forward to block but he misses there. The keeper, Niroshan, collects the ball and whips the bails off. They appeal for a stumping and the umpires take it upstairs to have a look. The replay is in and it is being examined multiple times. It takes a long time as it is very difficult for the third umpire to make a decision. The question - whether du Plessis' foot was in the air, when the stumping was effected - is something that looks to be very difficult to comprehend on the replays. Finally, as it is inconclusive, the third umpire deems that in the batsman's favour. Benefit of the doubt goes in the batsman's favour, remenmber?
An appeal for stumping. Faf du Plessis is the man in question. Is his foot in the air when the bails were taken off?
Good length ball on the stumps, defended.

Ohhh.. a nasty delivery there. It is a back of a length ball outside off, it pitches and bounces sharply. Goes well past the outside edge of Faf's bat as he looked to defend that. Beats the keeper as well and goes behind him for a bye.
Good length ball on off, Keshav looks to work it to the leg side but gets an inside edge there. It goes off his pads, to the on side, for a single.

BEATEN! Not much of a pressure delivery though, that one. Full and outside off, Keshav Maharaj hangs his bat outside the line of the stumps, looking to defend. He though misses and the ball goes past his outside edge.
Short and outside off, cut through point. And they come back in for the second. Excellent running.

Full and down the leg side, Maharaj helps it down towards fine leg. Picks up two there and gets to his 50. His 3rd in Tests. And he has a look at the heavens there. His strike rate has been very impressive too.
Dimuth Karunaratne is back on.

FOUR! Superb timing. Placement was perfect as well. Faf du Plessis now moves into the 190s with that. Shorter and outside off, FP rocks back and punches that through the covers. Places it well wide of deep extra cover as well.
Outside off, hit straight back to the bowler.
Du Plessis pushes this tossed up ball outside off through the covers for a couple.
Outside off, punched to sweeper cover for a single.
Full and outside the off stump, Faf du Plessis gets down and nudges it down to long off for a single. Looks like he is tired as he was looking a bit slow, when getting down.
Full and outside off, stroked straight to cover.
131 overs have been completed. South Africans are 577/6, with the lead now worth 181. Full and on the stumps, keeping low, defended to the on side well by Keshav.
Full and outside off, kept out to cover. KM flashes a thumbs up to his partner at the other end, on the follow-through.
Good length ball outside off, tapped down to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Keshav Maharaj jumps a little and taps it to cover.
Nicely played. Full and outside off, driven through the covers, to sweeper cover, for one.
Full and outside the off pole, blocked to the off side. Du Plessis was solid in his defence there.
Outside off, dabbed to point.
The 100-run partnership is up now. 3rd one in this innings for South Africa. Flat and outside off, du Plessis nudges it through the covers, to sweeper cover, for a single.
On the shorter side outside off, Faf rocks back and taps that to cover.
Floated outside off, nudged behind square on the off side for a single.
Wanindu floats this outside off, defended to the off side. A loud 'no' from Maharaj follows there.
Flatter and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone.
Fullish and outside off, du Plessis looks to power that on the off side but ends up mistiming it there.
Full and outside off, Faf presents the full face of his bat and drives but finds mid off there.
Fullish and around off, du Plessis nudges that behind square on the leg side for a couple.
Fullish and outside off, stabbed to cover.
Full and outside off, pushed down to mid off.
Fullish and outside off, stabbed to point for a single.
Full, around off, pushed down to mid on for a run. Takes Faf into the 180s.
Outside off, pushed to cover.
Fullish and outside off, pushed to the off side for a single.
Tossed up outside off, pushed down to long off for a run.
Short and outside off, stroked to sweeper cover for a single.
Wanindu Hasaranga to bowl from the other end.
That is an easy single there. Full and outside off, Keshav taps it to the off side for one.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Length delivery around off, du Plessis closes the face of his bat and glances it in front of square on the leg side for a single.

Full and outside the off pole, Keshav taps that to the off side and calls for a quick single. The fielder collects and throws it to the keeper's end. But Faf slides in and gets inside there. The ball too misses to hit the stumps though. Had it hit, might have been close.
Full and outside off, dabbed to the off side.
Full and on the pads, clipped to the on side.

We are back for the final session of Day 3. The Sri Lankan players are out in the middle. Faf du Plessis and Keshav Maharaj will resume their innings for South Africa. Dasun Shanaka will start the proceedings for this session.
... Day 3, Session 3 ...

South Africa would look to cross the lead of 200 to put pressure on Sri Lanka. On the other hand, Sri Lanka need wickets and would look to stop the run flow. Join us at 1500 local for the final session of Day 3.
On the other hand, Sri Lanka have looked tired and lost Kumara and Hasaranga due to injuries. However, Hasaranga came back and bowled some overs during the end of the session.
It has been an excellent session for South Africa. They have a lead of 169 runs. Faf du Plessis has looked solid and is on the verge of getting a double century. Maharaj has given him good support.
Fullish on middle, du Plessis clips it behind square on the leg side, down to fine leg. A brace. And the umpire removes the bail and says Tea. AND TEA IT WILL BE, ON DAY 3!
Shortish and outside off, hit down to long off for one.
Short and outside off, dabbed to the off side.
Short and outside off, cut in front of point for a single.
Full and outside off, pushed to cover this time.

FOUR! That is nicely played. Too easily put away. Full toss on off, Faf comes forward and drives that through the covers for a boundary. Gets it well wide of the rushing fielder from deep point as well.
Bouncer down the leg side, Keshav ducks under that one.
Fullish on middle, clipped to square leg for a single. FP moves to 170 now, from 234 balls. Looks like only he can get himself out.
Slower delivery, came out too loopy. Du Plessis, for a moment, almost thought it to be a beamer. It was on off and middle and Faf du Plessis backs away and strokes it to cover.
On off, du Plessis closes the face of his bat and glances it through mid-wicket for two runs.
This is hit to the leg side for a single.

Ohohoh.... almost took the umpire out there. Short ball, Faf swivels and pulls at it. The umpire at deep square leg does well to move away from the trajectory of the ball there. It goes to deep square leg for a single.
Looped up on middle, Maharaj closes the face of his bat, to flick to short mid-wicket. Looks to be in some pain still here, on the follow-through.
Tossed up on middle, clipped to the leg side.
Flatter and on off and middle, defended to the leg side.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and on off, stroked down to long off for a single.
Full toss outside off, stroked to cover.
Wanindu Hasaranga is back on.
Bouncer around middle, Maharaj ducks under it.
WIDE! Bouncer on middle, Maharaj does well to duck under it.
FOUR! Good shot! Full ball on off, Maharaj drives it through covers for a boundary.
Length delivery on off, Maharaj keeps it out.
Good length ball on off, Maharaj defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Maharaj blocks it well.
Good length delivery on off, Maharaj defends it off the front foot.
Full on off, Maharaj drives it through mid off for a run. SOUTH AFRICA LEAD BY 150 RUNS!
On off, du Plessis punches it through point for a single.
NO BALL! Tossed up delivery on off, du Plessis keeps it out. No Ball is signalled as Mendis whipped the bails off with his foot.
On middle, du Plessis plays a paddle sweep towards fine leg for a couple.
Floated delivery on off, du Plessis defends it to point.
Full ball on off, Maharaj drives it through mid off for a run.
Tossed up delivery on middle, du Plessis flicks it through square leg for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played! Full delivery on off, Maharaj drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Back of a length on off, du Plessis punches it through mid off for a single.
Length ball on off, du Plessis pushes it to point.
Good length delivery on off, Maharaj keeps it out.
Back of a length on off, Maharaj defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, du Plessis pushes it through point for a single.
Full and outside off, defended back to the bowler.
NO BALL! Kusal Mendis has overstepped here. Full and outside off, hit to cover.
SIX! This is a good shot! Short ball, KM rocks back and pulls this mightily over deep square leg for six runs.

A good throw might have had du Plessis there. Short and outside off, Keshav Maharaj camps back and strokes it down to the man at sweeper cover. He calls for two runs. The throw comes to the bowler's end but du Plessis is well back in by then.
Fullish on middle and leg, wristed to short mid-wicket.
Flat and outside off, Maharaj cuts it in front of point.
Very full on middle, driven to cover.
Down the leg side, Faf misses his glance.
Good length ball outside off, Keshav dabs it to cover-point for a single.
Good length ball outside off, defended to cover off the outer half.
Fullish and on the off pole, steered to third man for a single.
Shortish and on off, defended to the off side.
On off, blocked to mid on.
Fullish and just outside off, pushed down to long on for a single.
Outside off, cut to deep point for a single.
FOUR! Shot! Put away. It was a full toss, Maharaj swings it down to the wide long on boundary.
Outside off, nice, deft touch from Keshav. He dabs this behind square on the off side for a couple.
Tossed up around off, defended back to the bowler.
Full and around off, driven to cover.
Good length ball on the stumps, defended to the off side.
On off, this is worked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! First boundary for KM. Full and outside off, Keshav just pushes this through the covers and the ball goes away to the boundary.

An appeal for stumping but not given. Sri Lanka cannot even go upstairs. Down the leg side, Keshav Maharaj looks to turn it down to fine leg but misses. The keeper collects and whips the bails off and appeals for a stumping but nothing positive for Sri Lanka emerges.
Fullish on middle, kept out.
On off and middle, defended to the off side.
This is worked to deep point for a single.
Short and outside off, cut to point for a single.
Outside off, punched to point.

Some sharp turn there. Lands it around off, it pitches and moves away sharply, beating the outside edge of Faf who looked to play at that. It turned so sharply that it went to the outstretched arm of the fielder at slip. Dickwella appeals for a catch but later learns that it was on account of the turn and not the leading edge there.

FOUR! In the air for a while. Full and outside off, Faf du Plessis comes forward and strikes it uppishly. Short cover dives but fails to stop it. Long off runs to his left but fails to cut it off as well.
Loopy ball outside off, driven down to long off for a single.
Length delivery on off, defended to the on side.
Fullish on the stumps, nudged to the leg side.
Good length ball outside off, dabbed to cover.

Good length ball outside off, keeping low. Du Plessis is able to dab it wide of the man at cover. Takes one, says 'yeah,yeah' for the second, and gets it. 500 is up for South Africa. The lead now balloons to 105.
Back of a length ball outside off, Faf taps that to the off side.
Outside off, stroked though the covers for one.

Short and outside off, cut to deep point for two. Faf gets to his 150 here. It has been a really special innings from him. He has built on his 10th Test ton and will now be eyeing his first double here.
Flighted outside off, this is pushed down to long off for a single.

In the air... but safe. Floated delivery on middle, Maharaj looks to work it to the leg side but he ends up getting a leading edge there. It goes in the air but lands safely before the charging bowler, on the on side.
Mendis floats this outside off, defended to the off side.
Tossed up outside off, Keshav comes forward and looks to defend that but at the last minute pulls back from doing so. The ball goes just wide of his bottom edge, to the keeper.
Flat and outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, stroked firmly but straight to mid off there.
Full and around off, defended to cover.
Good length ball outside off, nudged to the man at gully.
Length delivery on off, du Plessis defends it out.
WIDE! A wayward bumper outside off, Faf lets it be. Wide called by the umpire there.
Full and on off, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
An appeal for LBW but not given. Height! Good length ball angled into the off stump line, Keshav lets it be and gets hit on his front pad. An appeal follows but to no avail there.

Hello and welcome to Day 3 of the first Test between South Africa and Sri Lanka. The hosts trail by 79 runs and would look to wipe out the deficit in the first place and get into the lead. What to look forward to on Monday? Can Sri Lanka break the Faf-Bavuma stand quickly? They are then into the bowlers. Of course, Mulder can bat but he is inexperienced. The pitch has already started to show signs of indifferent bounce and South Africa will have to bat last. So they need at least another 150 runs from here to ensure safety. The Lankans will hope that Rajitha is fit to bowl. Join us then on 28th December, 2020 at 10 am local (0800 GMT) for all the action from Day 3. ADIOS! TAKE CARE!

Never a better way to assert dominance. If Sri Lanka got things rolling on Day 1, South Africa transferred the pressure back in a matter of two hours. The opening stand of 141 in just under 29 overs set the tone. And then after the collapse, du Plessis and Bavuma ensured that the home team ends the day on a strong note.

Normally, you see teams buckling under pressure while chasing 400, even if they are batting for the first time in the match. But Elgar and Markram came out with amazing self-confidence and for a larger part of the day, the run rate was rattling along at 5 an over. Injuries hurt Sri Lanka, with Dhananjaya de Silva and Kasun Rajitha unavailable and had it not been for those burst of wickets after Tea, they might have been looking at a score of around 350. Dasun Shanaka was the most impressive, considering that he is not even a frontline bowler. Lahiru Kumara did well in the final session.

South Africa's day. First, they bowled out Sri Lanka within 11 overs and then just batted with confidence oozing. They have racked up more than 300 runs at a run rate of nearly 4.5 an over. The last session can be called as a shared one, because Sri Lanka won the first half, picking up 3/20 but then, nothing after that.
