Full and around off, eased down to long off for another single.
Outside off, pushed towards point for one.
That stays low again. It is outside off and Faf works it well, adjusting nicely, to get it through mid-wicket for a run.
Fuller, around middle, pushed towards long off but Hasaranga dives to his left to stop the ball.
Floated outside off, blocked to the off side.
Tosed up outside off, pushed towards long off for a single.

FOUR! 50-run stand up and frustration for Kumara. He lands this on a length outside off and makes du Plessis play. He then generates an outside edge too. The ball flies past second slip and into the third man fence.

Overpitched, around off, Temba drives it straight back but Kumara gets down against his followthrough and deflects it towards mid on, keeping the batsmen to a single. The deficit is now 129. 109 balls left in the day, 49 minutes remaining (extended).
Outside off, pushed towards cover.
Oho! Another ripper. Kumara lashes out a short ball, outside off and Bavuma has both his feet in the air, trying to evade it. That is called a rip-snorter.
Shorter in length, pulled through mid-wicket but there is protection in the deep. Just a run. Du Plessis moves to 20 now.
Outside off, tapped towards point for a single.
FOUR! Once again, Hasaranga errs on the shorter side and pays the price for it. Faf is too good a player to miss out on such lollipops. Goes back and works it through mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, driven towards long off for a single. The stand moves to 40.
Landed around middle, spinning away, well defended.
Outside off, a bit of a loop, left alone.
Outside off, pushed to the off side.
Full and around off, watchfully defended. 119 balls left in the day, 52 minutes remaining (extended).

FOUR! SUBLIME! That is such a good shot in the context of what he faced on the previous ball. Kumara gets a bit too greedy and overpitches. But Faf is ready, as he drives this through mid on. The deficit is now 137.
Another ripper. This is again, full but perhaps vey close towards off stump. FdP looks to play but the ball suddenly kicks up, beating the outside edge.
Full and just outside off, blocked towards mid on.
Fuller, outside off, but still wide to make Faf play. He shoulders arms.
Vishwa Fernando is seen going towards the dressing room. He might be done for the day.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length, outside off, pressed towards backward point.
Lahiru Kumara returns. 12-0-58-1 so far.
Tosed up, outside off, well kept out.
Full and outside off, solidly pressed out.
On middle and off, well defended.
Full and around off, watchfully defended. 129 balls left in the day, an hour's play left (extended).
Looks like there is an issue. The umpire is informing the players that Hawk Eye is down and cannot come into use for some time. They need to reboot the system.
Around off, Temba lunges to defend.
FOUR! A nice gift. A low full toss, outside off, Bavuma wrists it between mid on and mid-wicket. Moves to 23 from 27 balls.
A short ball, outside off, let through.
On a length, outside off, solidly defended.

FOUR! Nicely played. Full and down the leg side, du Plessis tickles it to the fine leg fence. The stand moves to 31 from 46 balls while Faf moves to double figures. 250 UP FOR SOUTH AFRICA. They now trail by 145.
Short and outside off, punched towards cover.
On a length, outside off, worked through square leg for a couple. The deficit is now 149.
On a length, outside off, well defended.
FOUR! CRACK! Interesting shot. Full and outside off, Bavuma gets down and mows a slog sweep over mid-wicket!
Floated outside off, pushed towards point.
Around off, pushed towards mid off.
Full and outside off, driven towards mid off.
FOUR! That is off the edge. Landed outside off, Bavuma looks to cut but the ball spins away and takes the outside edge. It flies past slip towards third man.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.
Lovely delivery. On a length, outside off, du Plessis looks to cut but the ball pitches and then zooms away, to beat him.
This is worked through square leg for a single.
Another in-dipper, Bavuma looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
On a length, outside off, worked through mid-wicket for a single.
This one darts back in, from outside off, du Plessis defends towards mid on.
Full and outside off, left alone. 149 balls left in the day, 78 minutes remaining (extended).
This stays extremely low, from a shorter length, Bavuma cuts it towards point.
Full again, watchfully blocked out.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Around off, solidly defended.
Full and around off, eased towards mid on again.
A short ball, around off, pushed towards mid on.
On a length, outside off, let through.
Half volley outside off, du Plessis leans and drives it through the covers but the fielder dives to his right and parries it to mid off.
Outside off, left alone.
A tad short, du Plessis looks to help it fine down the leg side but misses. The ball hits his pads and goes to the keeper. 159 balls left in the day, 83 minutes remaining (extended).
Full and around off, blocked towards mid-wicket.
On a length, but wide outside off, left alone.
Outside off, pressed towards cover.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Around off, Bavuma lunges and blocks. A no ball has been signalled.
On middle and off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter outside off, left alone.
Outside off, punched wide of mid off for a single.
Full and around off, worked towards short mid-wicket.
Full and around middle, stays low, Faf is hit on the pads and there is a mild LBW appeal. Turned down. Perhaps going down leg. No review thoughts. A leg bye taken.

FOUR OVERTHROWS! This helps in adding of the runs to the scoreboard. Outside off, Bavuma taps it towards point. He immediately calls for the single. Dasun Shanaka gets to it from gully, picks it up, has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. There is a back up but Lahiru Kumara at mid on gets a bad bounce and he let it through. Bavuma moves to 10 from 7 balls. The stand moves to 12 from 10 balls.
On a good length, outside off, coming in a long way, Temba shoulders arms, knowing perfectly well where his off stump is.
Outside off, on a length, well defended.
FOUR! Nice shot. Short of a length, outside off, Bavuma goes back and cuts it behind square on the off side for a boundary. The deficit is now 169.
On a length, outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, watchfully dead-batted.
Around off, whipped away but straight to short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, du Plessis leans and drives it wide of cover for a couple.
Outside off, pushed through the covers for a single to get off the mark.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Temba Bavuma walks in at number 6, replacing his skipper.

OUT! EDGED TO SLIP! De Kock is gone on the first ball he faces from spin. He looks totally flummoxed. Hasaranga gets his first for the match. Was this a googly? Or perhaps a leg spinner which did not spin. De Kock went on his back foot to defend but all he managed is a thick outside edge. Nice catch by substitute Lahiru Thirimanne at first slip. South Africa have lost 3/20 since Tea!
Double bowling change. Wanindu Hasaranga to bowl. 10-1-49-0 so far.
Around middle, helped through mid-wicket for a run. The stand moves to 20 from 20 balls.
Full and outside off, left alone.
FOUR! CLOUT! A short ball, down the leg side, de Kock swivels and pulls it to the fine leg fence. The deficit is now 177.
A length ball, down the leg side, Faf gets across to tuck but misses. The ball misses his pads and the batsmen take a leg bye.
Oops... looks like we missed it. Vishwa Fernando is bowling. 10-1-36-1 before this over.
Outside off, pushed towards cover for a single.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Fuller and around off, du Plessis comes forward to defend but the ball kicks up from there. He is forced to take his bottom hand off the bat.
Around off, well blocked out.
Down the leg side, Faf gets across and looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads.
Full and outside off, shoots low, watchfully kept out. 189 balls left in this session.
Outside off, driven towards mid off.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
FOUR! De Kock has raced to 12 from 5 balls. A short ball, around middle, de Kock pulls this away nicely, through mid-wicket. The stand moves to 13 from 8 balls.
A full toss, outside off, worked wide of mid on. The fielder does well to get across to his right and stop the ball. A single taken to get Faf off the mark.
A bouncer, outside off, ducked under.
Full and down the leg side, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
On a length, around off, watchfully defended.
FOUR! Thank you very much. Short and outside off, de Kock punches this behind point and gets his first boundary on his second ball. The deficit is now 189.
On middle and off, solidly defended.
And he is up and running straightaway. Around middle, on a length, de Kock whips this through mid-wicket. The fielder runs after it and stops it just inside the ropes. Three runs taken.
The skipper, Quinton de Kock, joins Faf.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Wow. Two wickets in the space of 5 balls. Two new batsmen in the middle. What a lift this will be to Sri Lanka's spirits. Full and outside off, Elgar looks to drive it straight back, but is unable to keep it down. Also, he is a touch away from the ball, which makes him close the bat face early. Normally, one gets away with such shots. But Shanaka is an excellent athlete. He takes a stinger to his left using both hands. Elgar cannot believe his luck. He just stands there, smiling, wishing what could have been, had he scored 5 more runs and got his 13th Test century.
Outside off, on a length, let through.
Full and outside off, stays low, Elgar watches it till the last moment and pushes it towards point.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
In walks the ex-skipper, Faf du Plessis.

OUT! Edged and taken by the keeper! This is what a little bit of consistency can do. Throughout the day, Sri Lanka have been struggling to be disciplined and bowl consistent lines and lengths. Since Tea, Kumara has found something and eventually, been rewarded. It is just short of full, very close to the off stump, making the batsman play at it and then, shape it away. From Rassie van der Dussen's point of view, he gets half forward. Normally, one does that when he is not sure whether to play at it or let it go. The bat just comes a little forward but in a hesitant manner. As a result, the outside edge is taken.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, on a length, let through.
Another short ball, helped behind square leg for a single.
A bumper, way too short, ducked under.
A short ball, down the leg side, fended to leg gully.
Misfield. By Lahiru Kumara. Rassie pushes this towards mid on but Kumara fumbles and the ball goes through. Two runs taken by the time he can recover.
Fuller and around off, well defended.

That is a ripper. Shaun Pollock (on air) is so impressed with this bowling, that he remarks that this entire over should be a part of the highlights package for the day! Length ball, outside off, van der Dussen commits himself into the forward push but the ball rears up suddenly. Beats him comprehensively.
On a length, outside off, left alone.
Around off, solidly defended.

BEATEN! How many times did we use this word in the last two sessions combined? You might get those by a simple CTRL + F. Very rarely. Full and outside off, van der Dussen is forced to push at it but the ball straightens and beats the outside edge.
That is very well fielded. A short ball, at the ribs, Elgar hops and plays it wide of short leg but the fielder dives to his left and stops the ball.

FOUR! Bowling to the field, reacting well with the bat but a poor effort in the field. A short ball, down the leg side, with a short leg and leg gully in place, Elgar does well to pull it all along the ground, well wide of leg gully. Now, Kusal Perera is the man at deep backward square leg. He gets to the ball but then makes a mess of it while diving. The deficit is now under 200.
A cracking short ball, right at the ribs but Dean plays it nicely, hopping in the air and well in front of short leg.
Okay. We have a field change. A helmet is being called for. Short leg is in place. Kumara does have the pace to make the batsmen hop.
A terrific short ball. Elgar is surprised and plays it very awkwardly, towards square leg.

No idea why it took 2 minutes to bowl this ball. No discussion. No sight-screen adjustment. No field changes. Still, so much time. Sri Lanka are trying to slow the game down.  A bouncer, on middle, Elgar ducks.
The breeze is picking up now. Should be good for the players. Only we hope that it does not bring the dark clouds in this direction.
Full and down the leg side, flicked towards fine leg for a single.
On middle, pushed towards mid on this time.
Full and around middle, pushed back to the bowler.

FOUR! That is just a push. Supreme timing. Full and around middle, Elgar leans across and just clips it through mid-wicket. However, once he beats the fielder there, the ball races across the turf. 50-STAND UP IN 66 BALLS! Elgar is into the 90s now.

FOUR LEG BYES. A bit too straight, targetting the stumps, Elgar gets across, looks to tuck but misses. However, the ball races off his back thigh, well past the keeper to the fine leg fence. The deficit is now 208.
Full and outside off, Elgar gets across and blocks.
On a length, outside off, pushed towards point.
Dasun Shanaka to partner Kumara. 7.5-0-33-0 so far.
A full-pitched ball, outside off, shouldered arms to.
Around off, on a length, defended watchfully. 229 balls left in the day.
Full and just outside off, again, this one does not bounce, Rassie adjusts by coming well forward and blocking.
Outside off, a full toss, left alone.

FOUR! PRISTINE! And now, there is that inconsistent length. Kumara tries to repeat what he bowled on the previous ball but dishes out a wide half volley. This time, van der Dussen is prepared. Watches the ball carefully, leans, gets his front foot across, right to the pitch of the ball and drives it through the covers. The stand moves to 43 from 58 balls.

EDGED, DOES NOT CARRY! There is that inconsistent bounce. Full and outside off, van der Dussen looks to push but there is no feet movement. Also, there is less bounce. The ball takes the outside edge but dies down on its way to the keeper.

The Lankan players get into a huddle. They need to remind themelves that they are not out of this game. 216 is still a lot of runs and it will be South Africa who will be batting last. A couple of wickets and the feeling will be high. There a few dark clouds in the horizon and we could have some thundershowers in the evening. Hopefully, the forecast is proved wrong. The players are out in the middle. LAHIRU KUMARA TO RASSIE VAN DER DUSSEN first up. Here we go...
... DAY 2, SESSION 3 ...

What to expect in the last session? 39 overs. No, don't think we will have so many of those bowled, unless Sri Lanka release an array of spinners. They might want to quieten the Proteas a touch. Get a few tight overs going, try and stifle the rate and then see if a false shot comes. The pitch has started to show signs of indifferent bounce, so the home side will want to make the most of tonight and tomorrow. If they bat the way they have been batting, do not rule out even 300 by Stumps. Join us back at 3 pm local (1300 GMT).

Well, Sri Lanka are two bowlers down. Dhananjaya de Silva got ruled out of this Test and series this morning, while Kasun Rajitha pulled out after bowling just 13 balls. So the tourists are short of bowlers but that is not South Africa's problem. They can only play what they get and they have done really well. Even the usually quiet Elgar has gone at a strike rate of more than three quarters of a 100. Markram played confidently, looking to set the tone but fell to a loose shot. But South Africa have plenty of batting to come.
What a session for the home side. 135/1 in 27 overs! That is at a whopping rate of 5 an over. The innings run rate is 4.73. Talk about the fighting spirit, do you need a better example?
Outside off, on a length, left alone. TEA ON DAY 2, SOUTH AFRICA TRAIL BY 216!
Full and outside off, DE walks across and then plays it to the leg side.
Full and outside off, Dean comes forward and presses it towards cover.
Outside off, on a length, let through.
Full and around middle, pushed towards mid on.

FOUR! Meandering bowling. No pace, no length, no line. Slow, full and down the leg side, Elgar tickles it behind square leg. Poor Lahiru Kumara, who just bowled a quick over, has to run to his left and dive. Comes second best. Worse, he does not even want to get up. He looks flat. The deficit is now 216.
Possibly the last over before Tea. Felt that the clock had already ticked past 2.40 pm local (1240 GMT) but it is not the case, one guesses.
Outside off, on a length, let through.
Outside off, pushed through cover for a single.

FOUR BYES! 'Aiyyo!' is what Dickwella would be thinking about this ball. This seems more like a bouncer in frustration from Kumara and he bangs it right in the middle of the pitch. Elgar ducks but he needn't have to. The ball shoots up like a missile and poor Dickwella leaps full stretch. Gets a glove to it but can do nothing to stop the ball.
FOUR! CLUNK! A short ball, outside off, Elgar gets on his toes and pulls it with aplomb through mid-wicket. Moves to 81 in 104 balls, with his 13th boundary. The stand is worth 30 now, in 47 balls.
Fuller outside off, Elgar looks to drive but the ball barely bounces and goes beneath the bat. Does not even carry to the keeper.
A length ball, around off, tapped to the leg side.
Action replay of the previous delivery.
Outside off, on a length, let through.

FOUR! Shanaka goes for the glory ball this time. He wants to get a full and straight, you-miss-I-hit LBW, but the angle makes the ball pitch around leg. All van der Dussen has to do is get bat on it and tickle it past the diving Dickwella to the fine leg fence. The deficit is now 229.
This is a better delivery. It is fuller, wider outside off, enticing the batsman to drive. However, van der Dussen has his wits about him and shoulders arms.
Gentle medium pace, short of a length, wide outside off, waste of a delivery, left alone.
Full and around off, flicked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Around 10 minutes to go to Tea. Karunaratne turns to Dasun Shanaka in the hope of a wicket. Elgar, preferably. 5.5-0-24-0 so far for Shanaka.
A bouncer to end the over, Rassie ducks.
A short ball, outside leg, now Elgar hops and tucks it through square leg for one.
A short ball, outside off, van der Dussen hops and helps it through square leg for a run. The stand moves to 20 from 36 balls.
On a length, outside off, punched through the covers for a single.
Full and down the leg side, flicked towards short mid-wicket.
On a length, outside off, solidly defended.
Full and around off, watchfully played out.
Short and down the leg side, helped through square leg for a single.

Is that a boundary? The fielder has put in a dive at deep mid-wicket. However, while trying to push the ball away, was his body touching the ropes? Too close to call. Add to it, his own shadow is marring the effort. There is one angle, which seems to indicate that his right shoe might have been touching the ropes with the ball in contact with his back. Boundary signalled.

FOUR! Good effort in the deep though. Full and around middle, Elgar works it through mid-wicket. The fielder comes running to his left, dives and then pushes the ball away. Now, the umpires want to check whether he has touched the ropes in doing that. The camera angles do no favour to the third umpire and it is very difficult to tell. Eventually, the third umpire seems convinced with one angle which indicates that the fielder's right shoe was touching the ropes, while his body was touching the ball. Unlucky for the fielder.
Shorter in length, worked towards square leg.
Around off, full again, flicked straight to Chandimal this time.
Full and outside off, Elgar flicks it through mid-wicket but Dinesh Chandimal dives to his right and stops the ball.
On a length, outside off, van der Dussen looks to drive but the ball goes off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
A bouncer, outside off, Rassie sways away from the line.
Low full toss, outside off, driven straight to cover.
Outside off, short in length, fended to the off side.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle and leg, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Lahiru Kumara comes back to bowl. 5-0-29-0 so far. Vishwa Fernando goes off the field as well. Hope he is alright.
On middle, worked through mid-wicket for a run.
FOUR! CLUBBED! Short and outside off, Elgar rocks back and pulls it over a ducking short leg for a boundary! 150 UP FOR SOUTH AFRICA. They trail by 244 runs. This stand is worth 11 from 19 balls now.
Outside off, eased through the covers for a single.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Shorter and quicker, outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, spinning in, helped through fine leg for a single. The deficit is now 249.
On a length outside off, coming in, pushed wide of mid off for a run.
Short and wide outside off, Elgar misses out, cutting it straight to point.
Wide. A wild bouncer, way too short and high, easily ducked under.
Full and outside off, coming in, watchfully pushed towards point.
Landed outside off, pushed through the covers for a single.
Landed outside off, gentle outswing, but too wide to trouble a new batsman. Shouldered arms to.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Short and down the leg side, helped through fine leg. Good diving stop by the fielder. A single to help van der Dussen get off the mark.
Full and around middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
Outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Down the leg side, helped through square leg. There is a lot of commotion, mainly from the keeper Dickwella but the single is easily completed in the end.
Full and around middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Another length ball outside off, Rassie shoulders arms to this one. A good over for the Lankans comes to an end.
Outside off, left alone.
Who walks in now? Rassie van der Dussen, it is.

OUT! CAUGHT! Sri Lanka finally get the wicket that they were searching for and they finally break this opening stand! He was looking good so far and has also scored 68 but his stint out in the middle comes to an end! Fernando dishes a good length delivery outside the off pole again. This time, Markram is tempted into the shot after being watchful in leaving balls in these areas alone. He throws his bat at this one but it proves to be his downfall. The ball takes the outside edge and flies towards Dasun Shanaka at gully, who is not going to drop this. Aiden looks at the heavens in frustration. Jersey number 68 takes out a man who was on 68.
Another good length delivery in the channel outside off, Aiden watchfully raises his blade and lets this one through.
In the channel outside off on a good length, Markram has no issues in leaving this one alone.
Short of a length and around the middle pole, Elgar tickles this one to the deep square leg region for a single.
Floated on middle, tucked around the corner, behind square on the leg side, for a run.
Flat and just outside off, Aiden nudges it through the covers for one.
Flatter and around the off stump line, defended off the outer half, to the off side.
Shortish and around off, pushed to the off side.
FOUR! This time, through the on side. Full and on the off stump line, Markram wrists it wide of a diving mid on fielder and gets a boundary.
FOUR! That is wonderfully played. Beautiful touch. Short and wide outside off, Aiden waits and waits and then cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
Full and outside off, left alone by Dean there.
Fullish and outside off, nudged wide of point for a single.
Full and outside off, Aiden Markram looks to drive that on the off side but gets an inside edge onto his pads. He needs to be really careful here.
Full and around off, solidly defended by Markram.
Full and outside off, the right-hander shoulders arms to this one.
Full and seaming in close to the off stump, Aiden leaves it alone.
Floated on off, tapped to the off side.
On middle, clipped to short mid-wicket.
Flighted around off, pushed to cover.
Floated on middle, knocked to the on side.
Down the leg side, Dean goes back and looks to work it behind square on the leg side, but he misses.
Full and just outside off, stabbed to mid on.

DRINKS! Well, well, what to say of the South Africans' batting here? They are simply coasting! They are going at over 5 rpo and both their openers have gone past their fifties. A partnership of 129 at the very start (and still going strong) bodes well for the hosts. They would look to continue the same tempo after the mini-break as well. Let's see if they can do so...

An appeal for LBW but nothing results. Good length ball angled into middle and leg, Markram lets it be and gets hit on the pads. A mild appeal follows but to no avail. Again, height being an issue. Dimuth does not press for a review.
Good length ball on the stumps, defended to the off side off the outer half.

BEATEN! Beautifull ball there. Good length delivery outside off, Aiden looks to defend but misses to do so there. The question though is, can Vishwa stay in that line? Can he bowl an over or so there?
Good length ball around off, Elgar closes the face of his bat and flicks it through mid-wicket. He calls for two but just gets one there.
FOUR! Four more. Beautifully played. In total control there, DE. Just look at the timing there. Shortish and around off, Dean closes the face of his bat to flick it through square leg for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, worked to mid on for a single.

FOUR! DEAN ELGAR GETS TO HIS 15TH TEST FIFTY! Shorter and on the off pole line, Dean Elgar rocks back and swings it through square leg. A fielder does give chase but fails to stop it. Three boundaries on the trot for Dean here.
FOUR! Excellent batting. Short and wide outside off, Dean Elgar goes on the back foot and cuts it through cover-point for a boundary.
FOUR! Well maneuvered. Away for four. Shorter in length, around off, Elgar camps back and pulls it wide of short fine leg for a boundary.
On the shorter side around off, Elgar rocks back and clips it to square leg.
Flat and on off, Dean goes back and taps it to short mid-wicket.
Fuller and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, driven to mid off, who gets to his right, dives and keeps it out. Well stopped, just the single there.

EDGED AND FOUR! It was close to gully, by the looks of it. Good length, outside off, drawing Elgar away from his body. He does so and looks to drive but gets it off the outside edge. It goes wide of gully and down to the third man boundary.
Fullish and outside off, stabbed to cover-point.
Good length ball outside off, squares Dean up. He manages to defend it off the outer half to backward point.
Full and outside off, driven through cover-point for a single.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Vishwa Fernando is back to bowl now. 5-1-19-0 are his numbers so far. A rookie bowler, let's see how he goes about now...
Full and around off, pushed down to long off for a single.
FOUR! That is nicely played. Full and on the pads, Aiden Markram closes the face of his bat and flicks it wide of the keeper, down to the fine leg fence.
Shorter and around off, Markram rocks back and keeps it out.

Floated on middle, glanced through mid-wicket for a single. And the 100 is up for South Africa. It is an important milestone for the openers as well. It is their 3rd 100-run stand. All of it, this season.
Tossed up on off, pushed back to Hasaranga.
Full toss to Elgar, he drives it down straight to mid off.
Lands it full outside off, it pitches and seams in, closer to off. Safe to be left alone though and Aiden does just that.
Short ball, outside off, left alone.
Length delivery around off, pushed back to the bowler.

An appeal for LBW but it results in nothing. Good length ball around off, Aiden looks to play at it but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal follows but to no avail and.... Oh... Markram does well there. The ball had fallen back on the surface and sensing that it might hit the stumps, Markram pushes it away with his boot. Good sense displayed by him. Good alertness.

WIDE AND FOUR! There is another one of those... Short and too high. It goes well over the shoulder of Aiden Markram. The Sri Lankan keeper jumps but the ball goes over him too, and into the long stop fence. Wide as well, signalled by the umpire.
Fullish and angled into off and middle, flicked in front of square on the leg side for a single.
BEATEN! Back of a length delivery well outside off, Dean goes after that but misses.
Short and outside off, Markram camps back and taps it back to the bowler.
Full and on the stumps, defended to the on side.
Shortish and around off, Markram goes back and pushes it on the off side.
Flatter and around off, Aiden rocks back and pushes it back to Wanindu.
Loopy on middle, nudged to the deep square leg region for a single.
On off, pushed to the off side.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR AIDEN MARKRAM! His 7th in Test cricket and a well deserved one! He has played wonderfully so far and the Proteas will be pinning their hopes on him to continue on! On a length on off, Markram punches this one through point and the ball speeds away to the ropes.
A bumper over middle, Markram ducks under this one.
A full ball and on off, Aiden squeezes this one out to the point region.
Length delivery and around off, Aiden is solid in his defense.
On off, glanced to mid-wicket for one.
Length delivery on off, Elgar blocks this one back to Lahiru.
Flatter and around off, punched to the cover region.
Flighted on off, Aiden defends this one out.

Sri Lanka started off well and were looking set to cross the 400-run mark but Lutho Sipamla had other plans as he picked up the three remaining wickets in quick succession and send the visitors packing with 396 on the board. It took an hour for the tailenders of the Islanders to lose their wicket but they did well to post a big total to their name. The disappointing thing for the visitors would be that Rajitha also walked off due to an injury and that could be a big blow to their plans.

A good first session of play comes to an end. Both the teams will be quite happy with where they stand at the moment. Sri Lanka might be slightly disappointed that they could not cross the 400-run mark but they will still be happy with their first innings total.

The South African skipper, Quinton de Kock, starts off by saying that he is feeling good. Adds that on Day 1, they were slightly disappointed with their bowling but that they came back nicely towards the end of their bowling spell and they showed great character to finish off nicely. Feels that it was a good start by Markram and Elgar and they showed great intent. Says that they are not looking to do anything too different in the next game.

Dimuth Karunaratne, the Sri Lankan captain, starts off by saying that they were in the driving seat as they scored nearly 400 and they did well as a batting unit. Credits his batters for their approach. Says that as a captain, they lost their main bowler and they did well in the first day but they have a couple of youngsters, who can come and do a job for him in the second test. Feels that they need to keep the momentum and a positive mindset and that the bowlers have done a good job for them, whenever the team has required them to. Tells that they want to take the positives from this game and move forward.

The Player of the Match is Faf du Plessis! He says that it was a good win and that they bowled alright but they showed good character as a batting unit and it is always good to contribute to the team. Adds that the important thing as a batting unit, is that they wanted to start well and they did that. Feels that he took his time to get going. Tells that as you look up at the scoreboard and see a deficit, you work on a partnership and then score more freely and they did that well. Feels that it was a good test match pitch and if you hit that channel while bowling, it would be good. Credits the groundsmen and adds that this was a free scoring match as well. Adds that he was feeling good in the lead up to this series and it was unique since he has not played red ball cricket in over a year and he wanted to just focus on the basics.

Tey took a lead of over 200 before declaring and from there on, it was a very difficult task for the Lankans to get back into the game. In the second innings, they kept losing wickets at regular intervals. Only Perera at the top and Hasaranga lower down the order showed some fight. The two scored half tons but a lot more was needed from them. In the end, it was a very one-sided game. Stay tuned for the presentation!

Then when South Africa came out to bat, the Lankans were dealt with another blow as they lost Rajitha in the initial overs itself due to injury! Then they kept drifting away from the game. The South African batters kept piling partnerships and that too in quick time. Three 100-plus run stands with Faf being the top scorer, falling one short of a double ton.

The Test started nicely for the visitors! They elected to bat and were set a good first innings total. However it could have been a few more had de Silva did not got injured. It was his partnership with Chandimal which looked at ease. However, once he walked off injured, Lanka kept losing wickets at regular intervals but they still amassed close to 400.

A very convincing win for South Africa in the end! Also, like predicted, this has turned out to be the last session. It was a no-brainer though as 2 wickets is all they needed. One though has to feel bad for Sri Lanka. They did not play as bad as the scorecard indicates. They were a lot better than that. Injuries though at crucial moments cost them big time. Not saying they would have won the game but it would have surely been a better contest.

A beauty to end! This lands on a length and around off, moves away after landing. Beats the outside edge of Chandimal's bat.
Length and around off, defended.
Extra bounce again! Length and outide off, it takes off after landing and also comes in with the angle. Chandimal does well to leave it by taking his hands away.
FOUR! First runs for today and it is in the form of a boundary. Good shot! Length and outside off, slightly fuller. Chandimal strokes it through covers and bags a boundary.
Length and around off, straightens a touch. Chandimal looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards gully.
Good carry to begin with! This is length and outside off, left alone. De Kock takes it at head height.

We are all set to begin! Some good news for Sri Lanka to begin with! Chandimal is walking out to bat which probably means he has recovered from the injury he suffered yesterday. He will resume his innings with Perera. Lungi Ngidi to begin proceedings for South Africa. Here we go...

Faf du Plessis is down for an interview. He says he has been getting too many 50s and 60s and wanted to go on. Further adds he does not feel too much into the thought of proving himself and just wants to do well for his side.Mentions he is physically and mentally very well at the moment. On not being the skipper, Faf does not feel that captaincy was a burden and he was enjoying it. He does not feel the bad form was because of him being captain.

It has been all South Africa in this Test after Day 1. They are well on course of winning this game today itself. The already have 2 players out and with a potential injury to Chandimal, they well could be five down already. A miracle is what they’ll need to actually save this game. Their first aim will probably be to avoid an innings defeat and they are still 160 runs away from doing so. We will find out if they avoid it. Stay tuned...
... Day 4, Session 1 ...

Now, Sri Lanka would look to play with a good, positive intent further. Their hopes of winning the match look slim, as things are, so, their common minimum plan now has to be to fend off the South African bowling. But the hosts will look to breathe down their neck on Day 4 and seal things in their favour. Can the Saffas close it on Day 4 or will the Lankans grit it out? Join us on Tuesday, 29th December 2020, at 1000 Local (0800 GMT) to find out. Until then, take care and bye.

Besides him, Vishwa Fernando snared 3 wickets and Shanaka and Kumara managed 2 and 1 wicket(s) respectively. After that, the visitors entered to bat, their 2nd innings. They encountered early setbacks, with their skipper, Dimuth, and Kusal Mendis falling early. After that though, Chandimal and Kusal Perera have done well to stabilize things.

And South Africa did not declare there, with Maharaj continuing strongly, looking for a maiden 100 in Test cricket. However, he departed for 73 and South Africa finished with 621 on the board, with a lead of 225 on board. There was nothing great to speak of the Lankan bowling, with folks going off the field, courtesy injuries. Hasaranga, who went off and came back later, was the pick, with 4 wickets to his name.

Earlier in the day, du Plessis and Bavuma took off from where they left. They got an overall partnership of 179 before Bavuma walked to a ball which he did not edge (as per Ultra Edge). After that, Faf du Plessis got good support from Wiaan and Keshav and that saw South Africa's lead grow by leaps and bounds. Du Plessis though could not get to his first double ton in Tests, as he fell 1 run short.

Right then, the men from South Asia still trail by 160 runs with 8 wickets in hand. A job remains to be done, not an easy one, but with Kusal Perera in the middle, he will look to motivate his side. And the Sri Lanka players will look to maintain a positive attitude as well, as that is the only thing that can be their saviour.

Full and on the pads, glanced down to fine leg for one. Chandimal limps, as he gets to the other end. Gosh, Sri Lankans cannot afford another injury here. Hope he's ok and will play tomorrow. For now, IT IS STUMPS ON DAY 3!
Good length ball around off, flicked to square leg for a single. That could actually have been a chance for run out but Maharaj is right-handed and he got the ball in his left hand there.
Great bit of fielding there from Wiaan Mulder. Full and around off, Perera drives it straight back to Wiaan, who gets down and does well to stop that.
Full and swinging away, to outside off, Kusal looks to work it to the leg side but ends up getting a leading edge there. It goes through the ground, down to mid on.
Back of a length and outside off, left alone.
Full and on middle, nicely clipped through mid-wicket there, a couple. Sri Lanka need to continue to bat aggressively.
Good length ball on top of the stumps, blocked.

FOUR! The men from the Island Nation need to be positive wherever they can. Short and outside off, Dinesh chases after that one. Throws the kitchen sink at it and gets it off a thick, uppish outside edge. It flies over the slip cordon and goes down into the third man fence.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, stroked firmly to cover for a single.

NOT OUT! South Africa had 3 reviews and they have lost 1 now. Length delivery on the pads, KP looks to help it down the leg side. To the naked eye, it seems to have hit his pads and gone to Quinton de Kock behind. The South African captain and all the Saffa players appeal for a caught behind. But the umpire is unmoved. Lungi Ngidi cajoles his skipper to take a review. And Quinny, after deliberating a little does so. But Ultra Edge lays their ambitions flat as there was no spike as the ball passed the bat there.
An appeal for caught behind! Kusal Perera is the man in question. Ultra Edge shows there is a flat line when the ball passes the bat.

BEATEN! Nicely bowled. Very nicely bowled from Ngidi. Lands it on a length and outside off, inviting Kusal Perera to drive. He does so but the ball whizzes past his outside edge and into the keeper's gloves.
Length delivery outside off, Chandimal lets that one be. 10 overs done and the Lankans are 56/2, still trailing by 169.
Shortish and outside off, Dinesh stands tall and punches it to the off side.
Good length ball on off, defended back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, whipped to short mid-wicket. Sri Lankans pinch in a quick single here.
On the pads, clipped to square leg.

Play and a miss! That is the dangerous delivery that Perera must be aware of. It lands on a full length outside off, pitches and seams away further, goes past the outside edge of Perera as he looks to play at that.
FOUR! Lovely shot. Just slightly overpitched. But what a beautiful example of a straight drive. It was just outside off, and DC comes forward and drives that through mid off for a boundary.
Full and outside off, driven to point.
Full and outside off, a one-handed cover-drive is out, straight to cover.
This one stays down. Shortish and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal hops and looks to drive that but ends up getting it off the inner half. It goes wide of short leg for two runs.
Fullish on middle, Chandimal is able to defend that but takes one hand off at the last minute, while doing so.
Outside off on a good length, dabbed to the slip cordon safely.
Good length ball on off and middle, defended.

FOUR! Nicely played. Too straight from Wiaan Mulder. It was on the pads and Kusal whips it uppishly through square leg. 'Catch' was the call but no one was there and the man at deep backward square leg runs to his right to cut off the boundary, but it was stroked well wide of him too.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball just outside off, defended to cover-point.
BEATEN! Cuts the batsman into half there. Lands it on a good length and outside off, it pitches and seams back in, Perera looks to play at it but the ball goes past his inside edge there.
Just outside off on a length, left alone.

NO BALL! Wiaan oversteps on his very first ball here. The umpires wanted to have a look at that for whether it was a correct ball or a no ball. No part of Mulder's foot was behind the line, it was deemed. Full and outside off, driven to cover.
An expensive over this. 14 off it. Good length ball, lands outside off and seams back in, Dinesh looks to play at it but misses and gets hit high on his pads there.
Angled into middle, this is worked to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Nice shot by Perera. Shortish and outside off, Kusal Perera throws his bat at it and gets it well wide of the fielder at point for a boundary.
Ohh... almost a catch there. Fullish and around off, Kusal strokes it uppishly. 'Catch' is the call to the man at mid off but it lands well ahead of him there.
Misfield and a couple. Length delivery around off, Kusal drives it to the right of mid off. The fielder gets there, dives, but fails to stop that. It goes through him and Sri Lanka pick up two.

Nicely played. Pushed into the off side by DC. Full and well outside off, Dinesh comes forward and gets his complete body weight behind the ball and drives it through the covers. A fielder gives chase and at the last moment, near the ropes, manages to push it back from going into the ropes. Three taken there.
Fullish length ball on middle, tickled down to fine leg for a single.
Length delivery outside off, left alone there.

FOUR OFF BYES! Quinton though applauds Nortje for that short ball. It was a bit too high and down the leg side, Dinesh Chandimal lets it be. De Kock jumps at full stretch but cannot stop that and the ball goes down to the fine leg fence.
FOUR! Well played. Good soft hands from Chandimal. Good length ball outside off, Dinesh Chandimal angles it between third and fourth slip and the ball races away to the third man boundary.
Full and outside off, Dinesh lets that one be.
Good length ball outside off, dabbed to the off side. Kusal says 'ya, ya, ya' and takes a single.
The physio is out in the middle. There is some issue with his leg. He is getting a strapping on his pad.
Full delivery on middle, Chandimal flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Dinesh Chandimal walks out to the middle now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ngidi gets his second and Sri Lanka are in trouble here! Good length delivery on off, Mendis looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards first slip where Rassie van der Dussen takes a good catch.
Back of a length on middle, Mendis looks to flick but gets a leading edge. It lands safely towards point.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Mendis looks to defend but misses it.
Back of a length on off, Mendis defends it to covers.
Length ball on off, Mendis blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Third boundary of the over! Full delivery on off, Perera drives it through covers for a boundary.
Back of a length on middle, Perera pushes it to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Perera blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Good shot! Full delivery on middle, Perera flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Terrific shot! Length ball on off, Perera punches it through point for a boundary.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Perera looks to defend but misses it.
Kusal Mendis is the new batsman in.
OUT! BOWLED! Ngidi strikes! Full delivery on off, Karunaratne looks to defend but misses it and gets bowled. It hits the off stump. That ball kept low there.
Back of a length on off, Karunaratne defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Good shot! Length delivery on off, Karunaratne pushes it through mid off for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Karunaratne looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
Short and outside off, Karunaratne looks to cut but misses it.
Length ball on off, Karunaratne blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Good shot! Full delivery on off, Perera drives it through covers for a boundary.
Length delivery outside off, Perera pushes it to point.
Back of a length on off, Kusal keeps it out.
Good length ball on off, Perera defends it off the front foot.
Down the leg side, Perera leaves it alone.
Back of a length on middle, Karunaratne flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Anrich Nortje to bowl from the other end.
A dot to finish then. Length ball angled into middle and leg, tucked to short leg safely.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Kusal Perera looks to play at that one but ends up getting an inside edge onto his pads.
Good length ball around off, Perera looks to play at it but misses and gets hit high on his pads.
Fullish and on the pads, Kusal looks to play at it but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Good length ball on off, blocked.
Good length ball on middle, flicked to deep backward square leg for a single.

We are all set to begin Sri Lanka's second innings. The South African players are out in the middle. Dimuth Karunaratne and Kusal Perera will open the innings for Sri Lanka. Lungi Ngidi will start the proceedings for South Africa.
